pe":"code","source":["import seaborn as sns\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","ax = sns.countplot(x=\"Churn\", data=df)\n","ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":449},"id":"VhFZaJR6mBNA","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343550952,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":31,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"15dacc5c-2ea4-4b1f-c6d3-d463b418c67d"},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","This visualization illustrates the distribution of the target variable, showing that 5,174 customers (approx. 73.5%) remained with the service while 1,869 customers (approx. 26.5%) churned."],"metadata":{"id":"TKbEKeJOf4F6"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["gb = df.groupby(\"Churn\").count()['tenure']  # count any column\n","plt.pie(gb.values, labels=gb.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')\n","plt.title(\"Percentage Of Churned Customers\",fontsize = 10)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":425},"id":"NJ2LRX9ynBIa","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343551021,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":64,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"e5162026-0698-4478-f518-beba6faef6e7"},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","This pie chart provides a clear breakdown of the dataset's composition, showing that 73.5% of customers (the \"No\" category) are retained, while 26.5% of the customer base has churned."],"metadata":{"id":"b8CtsjIjf-Su"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["plt.figure(figsize = (3,3))\n","ax = sns.countplot(x =\"SeniorCitizen\" , data = df)\n","ax.bar_label(ax.containers[0])\n","plt.title(\"Count of Customer By SeniorCitizen\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":333},"id":"J0wuVY0YCmaX","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343551248,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":233,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"7eca135c-1f87-4e91-c24e-e0045790d19f"},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 300x300 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","This demographic analysis shows that the vast majority of the customer base (83.8%) consists of non-senior citizens, while senior citizens represent a significantly smaller segment at 16.2%."],"metadata":{"id":"YtlVrzmMgBoY"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\n","\n","# Calculate percentages by gender and churn (100% stacked)\n","gb = df.groupby(['gender', 'Churn']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)\n","gb_pct = gb.div(gb.sum(axis=1), axis=0) * 100  # Convert to percentages\n","\n","# Plot stacked bars\n","gb_pct.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())\n","plt.title('Churn by Gender (100% Stacked)', fontsize=14)\n","plt.ylabel('Percentage (%)')\n","plt.xlabel('Gender')\n","plt.legend(title='Churn')\n","plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n","\n","# Add percentage labels on bars\n","for n, rects in enumerate(plt.gca().containers):\n","    for rect in rects:\n","        height = rect.get_height()\n","        if height > 0:\n","            plt.gca().text(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width()/2.,\n","                          rect.get_y() + height/2.,\n","                          f'{height:.1f}%', ha='center', va='center',\n","                          fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":507},"id":"-AAwz6ayAjXn","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343551688,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":438,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"6b7ed9d6-6ec8-4478-e85e-efdf48daa3f5"},"execution_count":18,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","This 100% stacked bar chart reveals that churn rates are nearly identical across genders, with 26.9% of females and 26.2% of males leaving the service."],"metadata":{"id":"9rClQg2WgOl_"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# comparitively higher number of people in SeniorCitizen has been churned out."],"metadata":{"id":"QbSVEegxBMuV","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343551691,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}}},"execution_count":19,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["plt.figure(figsize = (9,4))\n","sns.histplot(x = 'tenure', data= df , bins = 50)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":382},"id":"nXPyMwcqDbXx","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343552113,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":421,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"8a1f1d5d-1b69-465b-df4a-3957efaf4c81"},"execution_count":20,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 900x400 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","The tenure distribution reveals a bi-modal \"U-shape,\" highlighting high customer density in both the early-stage (0–5 months) and long-term loyalist (70+ months) segments."],"metadata":{"id":"j0v6z1ZKggu-"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["plt.figure(figsize = (3,3))\n","ax = sns.countplot(x =\"Contract\" , data = df, hue = \"Churn\")\n","ax.bar_label(ax.containers[1])\n","plt.xticks(rotation = 90)\n","plt.title(\"Count of Customer By Contract\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":432},"id":"Ij4C0kHREMLz","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343552687,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":568,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"63dcfbb4-6010-4724-bc13-3e0cfeea5102"},"execution_count":21,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 300x300 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","This chart highlights a critical link between contract length and attrition, showing that 1,655 customers (approx. 88.5% of all churners) are on Month-to-month plans"],"metadata":{"id":"DkzyC-mVg2fl"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["df.columns.values"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"IUnRzhdrHzd_","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343552708,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":14,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"5cdd36a5-b9e9-426a-dc0b-efe0544fd4f5"},"execution_count":22,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["array(['customerID', 'gender', 'SeniorCitizen', 'Partner', 'Dependents',\n","       'tenure', 'PhoneService', 'MultipleLines', 'InternetService',\n","       'OnlineSecurity', 'OnlineBackup', 'DeviceProtection',\n","       'TechSupport', 'StreamingTV', 'StreamingMovies', 'Contract',\n","       'PaperlessBilling', 'PaymentMethod', 'MonthlyCharges',\n","       'TotalCharges', 'Churn'], dtype=object)"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":22}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","# Your columns list\n","categorical_cols = ['customerID', 'gender', 'SeniorCitizen', 'Partner', 'Dependents',\n","                   'PhoneService', 'MultipleLines', 'InternetService',\n","                   'OnlineSecurity', 'OnlineBackup', 'DeviceProtection',\n","                   'TechSupport', 'StreamingTV', 'StreamingMovies']\n","\n","# Skip customerID (not useful for countplot)\n","plot_cols = [col for col in categorical_cols if col != 'customerID']\n","\n","# Create subplots (4 rows, 4 columns = 16 plots)\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 4, figsize=(20, 16))\n","axes = axes.ravel()  # Flatten 2D array to 1D for easy iteration\n","\n","# Plot countplot for each column\n","for idx, col in enumerate(plot_cols):\n","    if idx < len(axes):  # Ensure we don't exceed subplot count\n","        sns.countplot(data=df, x=col, ax=axes[idx])\n","        axes[idx].set_title(col, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n","        axes[idx].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n","\n","# Remove empty subplots\n","for idx in range(len(plot_cols), len(axes)):\n","    fig.delaxes(axes[idx])\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":625},"id":"1q5txndLLcAs","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343554978,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":2266,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"4c71595a-e6f1-48c5-869a-25f014d0d908"},"execution_count":23,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x1600 with 13 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The data shows a balanced mix of gender and partnership status, but highlights a significant opportunity for growth in service attachments, as over 40% of customers do not have features like Online Security or Tech Support."],"metadata":{"id":"TydIJMqkhFLs"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["plt.figure(figsize = (4,3))\n","ax = sns.countplot(x =\"PaymentMethod\" , data = df, hue = \"Churn\")\n","ax.bar_label(ax.containers[1])\n","ax.bar_label(ax.containers[1])\n","plt.xticks(rotation = 45)\n","plt.title(\"Churned Customes by  PaymentMethod \")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":456},"id":"Egy2Q1wLccgL","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773343555208,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":211,"user":{"displayName":"Krishiv Photo","userId":"01179342665673246410"}},"outputId":"ead04903-449d-4a80-e779-148cec655c3b"},"execution_count":24,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 400x300 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["This visualization reveals that Electronic check is the most volatile payment method, accounting for 1,071 churned customers, which is approximately 57.3% of all churners."],"metadata":{"id":"6mqdANk5hLFk"}}]}